				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E = 54.872 \ast h_b^{0.226}$$\end{document}For Si, the hb is about 80 nm and this value depends on parameters such as in-plain strain, Poisson’s ratio and the Young’s modulus of bulk Si. The nanometre range is hard to achieve with mechanical grinding or wet etching of bulk Si wafer, nonetheless with SOI wafers it is possible to obtain UTCs with nanometre thickness.

The mechanical strength of UTCs is also influenced by their thickness and the stress generated during the bending. Mathematically this is expressed as:4σst=E*h2R\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
